/\\_/\\   <--  ‚ÄúKitt‚ÄëOS‚Äù ‚Äì the tiniest cat‚Äëcentric kernel for Cortex‚ÄëM0+
  ( o.o )   --------------------------------------------------------------
   > ^ <    It lives in cache line‚ÄØ0, purrs at 7.3‚ÄØ√ó‚ÄØ10‚Åª¬π¬π‚ÄØHz, and
          never uses more than one block of flash.
Below is a complete, self‚Äëcontained ‚Äúkitten OS‚Äù that you can compile for a
Cortex‚ÄëM0+ (STM32F0, nRF51, etc.).
Everything fits into a single flash page, uses the 5‚Äëbyte .kitten file as
its only on‚Äëdisk data, and even stores the CRC‚Äë8 checksum (0x73) in the
